lead_paragraph: Tom Latham and Kane Williamson steered New Zealand to 43 for one in their second innings at tea on Monday, after Martin Guptill went for a duck, as the hosts reduced Australia's lead on the third day of the second test to 92 runs.

headline.print_headline: New Zealand Reduce Deficit to 92, Australia Get Guptill
